  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">On the synodal route: the protagonism of indigenous women in Puerto Maldonado</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The territorial assemblies and event participatory consultations leading to the Amazon synod identified a need and gap in the training and formation of indigenous women. They highlighted how women in the regions are often relegated to a secondary role in their communities, with little space for participation, leadership or voicing their opinion. Most of the communities are led by men and in some spaces women&apos;s opinions are not taken into account at all.
The project aims to strengthen the participation of indigenous Amazonian women of the Vicariate of Puerto Maldonado in order to make their voices heard and to enable the Amazonian Church to support the protagonism of indigenous women integrating the Synodal perspective and Pope&apos;s Amazon exhortation. The project aims to ensure, through training and accompaniment, that there are new women leaders and that existing ones are strengthened and can increase their voice and capacities, so that their rights as women and representatives of indigenous peoples can be defended, taking action in relation to human and indigenous rights, prevention of violence towards women and people trafficking.</narrative>
  </description>
